events.description: Battle of Nineveh: A Byzantine army under Emperor Heraclius defeats Emperor Khosrau II's Persian forces, commanded by General Rhahzadh.
events.html: • 627 – Battle of Nineveh: A Byzantine army under Emperor Heraclius defeats Emperor Khosrau II's Persian forces, commanded by General Rhahzadh.[1]

events.description: Maria of Enghien sells the lordship of Argos and Nauplia to the Republic of Venice.
events.html: • 1388 – Maria of Enghien sells the lordship of Argos and Nauplia to the Republic of Venice.[2]

events.description: Pennsylvania becomes the second state to ratify the US Constitution.
events.html: • 1787 – Pennsylvania becomes the second state to ratify the US Constitution.[3]

events.description: American Civil War: USS Cairo sinks on the Yazoo River.
events.html: • 1862 – American Civil War: USS Cairo sinks on the Yazoo River.[4]

events.description: Oaks explosion: The worst mining disaster in England kills 361 miners and rescuers.
events.html: • 1866 – Oaks explosion: The worst mining disaster in England kills 361 miners and rescuers.[5]

events.description: Joseph H. Rainey of South Carolina becomes the second black U.S. congressman.
events.html: • 1870 – Joseph H. Rainey of South Carolina becomes the second black U.S. congressman.[6]

events.description: Guglielmo Marconi receives the first transatlantic radio signal (the letter "S" [•••] in Morse Code), at Signal Hill in St John's, Newfoundland.
events.html: • 1901 – Guglielmo Marconi receives the first transatlantic radio signal (the letter "S" [•••] in Morse Code), at Signal Hill in St John's, Newfoundland.[7]

events.description: Yuan Shikai declares the establishment of the Empire of China and proclaims himself Emperor.
events.html: • 1915 – Yuan Shikai declares the establishment of the Empire of China and proclaims himself Emperor.[8]

events.description: Father Edward J. Flanagan founds Boys Town as a farm village for wayward boys.
events.html: • 1917 – Father Edward J. Flanagan founds Boys Town as a farm village for wayward boys.[9]

events.description: The Lebensborn Project, a Nazi reproduction program, is founded by Heinrich Himmler.
events.html: • 1935 – The Lebensborn Project, a Nazi reproduction program, is founded by Heinrich Himmler.[10]

events.description: Second Sino-Japanese War: USS Panay incident: Japanese aircraft bomb and sink U.S. gunboat USS Panay on the Yangtze river in China.
events.html: • 1937 – Second Sino-Japanese War: USS Panay incident: Japanese aircraft bomb and sink U.S. gunboat USS Panay on the Yangtze river in China.[11]

events.description: HMS Duchess sinks after a collision with HMS Barham off the coast of Scotland with the loss of 124 men.
events.html: • 1939 – HMS Duchess sinks after a collision with HMS Barham off the coast of Scotland with the loss of 124 men.[12]

events.description: Winter War: The Battle of Tolvajärvi, also known as the first major Finnish victory in the Winter War, begins.
events.html: • 1939 – Winter War: The Battle of Tolvajärvi, also known as the first major Finnish victory in the Winter War, begins.[13]

events.description: World War II: Fifty-four Japanese A6M Zero fighters raid Batangas Field, Philippines. Jesús Villamor and four Filipino fighter pilots fend them off; César Basa is killed.
events.html: • 1941 – World War II: Fifty-four Japanese A6M Zero fighters raid Batangas Field, Philippines. Jesús Villamor and four Filipino fighter pilots fend them off; César Basa is killed.[14]

events.description: The Holocaust: Adolf Hitler declares the imminent extermination of the Jews at a meeting in the Reich Chancellery.
events.html: • 1941 – The Holocaust: Adolf Hitler declares the imminent extermination of the Jews at a meeting in the Reich Chancellery.[15]

events.description: The People's Republic of Korea is outlawed in the South, by order of the United States Army Military Government in Korea.
events.html: • 1945 – The People's Republic of Korea is outlawed in the South, by order of the United States Army Military Government in Korea.[16]

entities.name: United States Army Military Government in Korea

events.description: United Nations Security Council Resolution 13 relating to acceptance of Siam (now Thailand) to the United Nations is adopted.
events.html: • 1946 – United Nations Security Council Resolution 13 relating to acceptance of Siam (now Thailand) to the United Nations is adopted.[17]

events.description: United Nations Security Council Resolution 121 relating to acceptance of Japan to the United Nations is adopted.
events.html: • 1956 – United Nations Security Council Resolution 121 relating to acceptance of Japan to the United Nations is adopted.[18]

events.description: Kenya declares independence from Great Britain.
events.html: • 1963 – Kenya declares independence from Great Britain.[19]

events.description: The Piazza Fontana bombing; a bomb explodes at the headquarters of Banca Nazionale dell'Agricoltura (the National Agricultural Bank) in Piazza Fontana in Milan, Italy, killing 17 people and wounding 88. The same afternoon, three more bombs are detonated in Rome and Milan, and another is found unexploded.
events.html: • 1969 – The Piazza Fontana bombing; a bomb explodes at the headquarters of Banca Nazionale dell'Agricoltura (the National Agricultural Bank) in Piazza Fontana in Milan, Italy, killing 17 people and wounding 88. The same afternoon, three more bombs are detonated in Rome and Milan, and another is found unexploded.[20]

events.description: The 8.2 Mw  Tumaco earthquake shakes Colombia and Ecuador with a maximum Mercalli intensity of IX (Violent), killing 300–600, and generating a large tsunami.
events.html: • 1979 – The 8.2 Mw  Tumaco earthquake shakes Colombia and Ecuador with a maximum Mercalli intensity of IX (Violent), killing 300–600, and generating a large tsunami.[21]

events.description: Coup d'état of December Twelfth occurs in South Korea.
events.html: • 1979 – Coup d'état of December Twelfth occurs in South Korea.[22]

events.description: Arrow Air Flight 1285R, a McDonnell Douglas DC-8, crashes after takeoff in Gander, Newfoundland, killing all 256 people on board, including 236 members of the United States Army's 101st Airborne Division.
events.html: • 1985 – Arrow Air Flight 1285R, a McDonnell Douglas DC-8, crashes after takeoff in Gander, Newfoundland, killing all 256 people on board, including 236 members of the United States Army's 101st Airborne Division.[23]

events.description: The Clapham Junction rail crash kills thirty-five and injures hundreds after two collisions of three commuter trains—one of the worst train crashes in the United Kingdom.
events.html: • 1988 – The Clapham Junction rail crash kills thirty-five and injures hundreds after two collisions of three commuter trains—one of the worst train crashes in the United Kingdom.[24]
